hmIOModuleGroup.description: The Hirschmann Private IO Module definitions for Platform devices.

hmIOModConfigDigInputAdminState.name: hmIOModConfigDigInputAdminState
hmIOModConfigDigInputAdminState.description: enables sending SNMP traps or log events on input change. (if disable(2) input task will do nothing).

hmIOModConfigDigOutputAdminState.name: hmIOModConfigDigOutputAdminState
hmIOModConfigDigOutputAdminState.description: enables polling of output values (if disable(2) output task will do nothing).

hmIOModConfigDigInputRefreshInterval.name: hmIOModConfigDigInputRefreshInterval
hmIOModConfigDigInputRefreshInterval.description: The refresh interval (in ms) of the input values. Minimum 500ms, Maximum 10000ms (10s).

hmIOModConfigDigOutputRefreshInterval.name: hmIOModConfigDigOutputRefreshInterval
hmIOModConfigDigOutputRefreshInterval.description: The refresh interval (in ms) of the output values. Minimum 500ms, Maximum 10000ms (10s).

hmIOModConfigDigOutputRetryCount.name: hmIOModConfigDigOutputRetryCount
hmIOModConfigDigOutputRetryCount.description: The retry count for the output values. when after the number of configured retries no SNMP get request was answered, the output value (hmIOModOutputValue) will be set to invalid (3). Minimum 1, Maximum 10.

hmIOModConfigDigInputTable.name: hmIOModConfigDigInputTable
hmIOModConfigDigInputTable.description: IO module config table for inputs

hmIOModConfigDigInputEntry.name: hmIOModConfigDigInputEntry
hmIOModConfigDigInputEntry.description: IO module config entry for inputs

hmIOModConfigDigInputModID.name: hmIOModConfigDigInputModID
hmIOModConfigDigInputModID.description: The module ID of an input.

hmIOModConfigDigInputLogEvent.name: hmIOModConfigDigInputLogEvent
hmIOModConfigDigInputLogEvent.description: Trigger an event log when input status changes. If the value is disable (2), no event log entry will be written. If the value is enable (1), an event log entry will be written when the input state changes. The input state will be checked acording to the refresh interval entered in hmIOModConfigDigInputRefreshInterval.

hmIOModConfigDigInputSnmpTrap.name: hmIOModConfigDigInputSnmpTrap
hmIOModConfigDigInputSnmpTrap.description: Trigger an SNMP trap log when input status changes. If the value is disable (2), no SNMP trap will be sent. If the value is enable (1), a SNMP trap will be sent when the input state changes. The SNMP trap will be sent to all receivers configured in hmAgentSnmpTrapReceiverConfigTable. The input state will be checked acording to the refresh interval entered in hmIOModConfigDigInputRefreshInterval.

hmIOModConfigDigOutputTable.name: hmIOModConfigDigOutputTable
hmIOModConfigDigOutputTable.description: IO module config table for outputs

hmIOModConfigDigOutputEntry.name: hmIOModConfigDigOutputEntry
hmIOModConfigDigOutputEntry.description: IO module config entry for outputs

hmIOModConfigDigOutputModID.name: hmIOModConfigDigOutputModID
hmIOModConfigDigOutputModID.description: The module ID of an output.

hmIOModConfigDigOutputLogEvent.name: hmIOModConfigDigOutputLogEvent
hmIOModConfigDigOutputLogEvent.description: Trigger an event log when output status changes. If the value is disable (2), no event log entry will be written. If the value is enable (1), an event log entry will be written when the output state changes. The output state will be checked acording to the refresh interval entered in hmIOModConfigDigOutputRefreshInterval.

hmIOModConfigDigOutputSnmpTrap.name: hmIOModConfigDigOutputSnmpTrap
hmIOModConfigDigOutputSnmpTrap.description: Trigger an SNMP trap log when output status changes. If the value is disable (2), no SNMP trap will be sent. If the value is enable (1), a SNMP trap will be sent when the output state changes. The SNMP trap will be sent to all receivers configured in hmAgentSnmpTrapReceiverConfigTable. The output state will be checked acording to the refresh interval entered in hmIOModConfigDigOutputRefreshInterval.

hmIOModConfigDigOutputSourceIP.name: hmIOModConfigDigOutputSourceIP
hmIOModConfigDigOutputSourceIP.description: The IP address of an input mirrored to the output. Use 0.0.0.0 if the output should not be set. In this case hmIOModOutputValue is invalid (3). Use 127.0.0.1 if an local input should be used.

hmIOModConfigDigOutputSourceModID.name: hmIOModConfigDigOutputSourceModID
hmIOModConfigDigOutputSourceModID.description: The module ID of an input mirrored to the output. Ignored when hmIOModConfigDigOutputSourceIP is 0.0.0.0.

hmIOModConfigDigOutputSourceID.name: hmIOModConfigDigOutputSourceID
hmIOModConfigDigOutputSourceID.description: The ID of an input mirrored to the output. Ignored when hmIOModConfigDigOutputSourceIP is 0.0.0.0.

hmIOModConfigDigOutputSourcePort.name: hmIOModConfigDigOutputSourcePort
hmIOModConfigDigOutputSourcePort.description: The SNMP port number being used by the input mirrored to the output. This port would be the destination for the SNMP requests for polling the state of the input.

hmIOModValueDigInputTable.name: hmIOModValueDigInputTable
hmIOModValueDigInputTable.description: IO module value table for inputs

hmIOModValueDigInputEntry.name: hmIOModValueDigInputEntry
hmIOModValueDigInputEntry.description: IO module value entry for inputs

hmIOModValueDigInputModID.name: hmIOModValueDigInputModID
hmIOModValueDigInputModID.description: The module ID of an input.

hmIOModValueDigInputValue.name: hmIOModValueDigInputValue
hmIOModValueDigInputValue.description: Status of the input. If the value is not-available(0), then the IO module is not plugged in, if the value is high(1), the input has high (+24V) value, if the value is low(2), the input has low (0V) value.

hmIOModValueDigOutputTable.name: hmIOModValueDigOutputTable
hmIOModValueDigOutputTable.description: IO module value table for outputs

hmIOModValueDigOutputEntry.name: hmIOModValueDigOutputEntry
hmIOModValueDigOutputEntry.description: IO module value entry for outputs

hmIOModValueDigOutputModID.name: hmIOModValueDigOutputModID
hmIOModValueDigOutputModID.description: The module ID of an Output.

hmIOModValueDigOutputValue.name: hmIOModValueDigOutputValue
hmIOModValueDigOutputValue.description: Status of the output. If the value is not-available(0), then the IO module is not plugged in, if the value is high(1), the output has high (+24V) value, if the value is low(2), the output has low (0V) value. If the value is invalid (3), the output has low (0V) value and the IO input source is configured but can not be read. If the value is not-configured (4), the output has low (0V) value and has no IO input source configured.

hmIOModDigInputChangeTrap.name: hmIOModDigInputChangeTrap
hmIOModDigInputChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent if the state of an input changes. This trap is sent only when hmIOModConfigDigInputSnmpTrap is set to enabled (1).

hmIOModDigOutputChangeTrap.name: hmIOModDigOutputChangeTrap
hmIOModDigOutputChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent if the state of an input changes. This trap is sent when hmIOModConfigDigOutputSnmpTrap is set to enabled (1) or when the output value changes from or to invalid (3)
